==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[hat#Old English|hāt]] + [[heorte]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ha:tˌheoɹt/

===Adjective===
'''hātheort'''
# [[fiery]], [[passionate]], [[furious]]
#:''Ðes gerefa is swiðe hatheort and he ðe wile forleosan'': this officer is very furious and he will destroy you.  (''Narratiunculae Anglice'')

